Package: massmatcher
Type: Package
Title: Massmatcher: a comprehensive mass matching tool for untargeted metabolomics
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Jiada", family = "Zhan", middle = "", "jzha832@emory.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2480-8760")
    )
  )
Maintainer: Jiada (James) Zhan <jzha832@emory.edu>
Date: 2025-06-16
Description: Massmatcher curates molecular information from metorigindb,
    PubChem, HMDB, KEGG, LIPID_MAPS, ChEBI, BioCyc, and DrugBank. The main
    focus is to annotate unknown m/z values based on theoretical
    monoisotopic mass and hypothetical adduct forms. After that, three
    options are offered to users: select only the quantified metabolites,
    select only the quantified and most abundant metabolites, and include
    chemical classification information for all annotations.
